==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tulipwood
<hw>Tu"lip*wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The beautiful
rose-colored striped wood of a Brazilian tree (<spn>Physocalymna
floribunda</spn>), much used by cabinetmakers for inlaying.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Queensland tulipwood</b></col>, <cd>the variegated wood
of an Australian sapindaceous tree (<spn>Harpullia pendula</spn>).</cd>
<rj><au>J. Smith (Dict. Econ. Plants).</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tull</ent>⟦br⟧
